STATE
v.
Colell B. STEELE. No. 208P14-1. Supreme Court of North Carolina. June 10, 2015. Mr. Colell B. Steele, Brunswick, for Steele, Colell Barion. Ms. Kimberly N. Callahan, Assistant Attorney General, for State of North Carolina. Mr. R. Andrew Murray, District Attorney, for State of North Carolina.

Opinion

The following order has been entered on the motion filed on the 23rd of June 2014 by Defendant to Appoint Counsel:

"Motion Dismissed as moot by order of the Court in conference, this the 10th of June 2015."
